Class RocketBody

java.lang.Object
SpaceObject
RocketBody
public class RocketBody extends SpaceObject
The RocketBody class represents a rocket body in space. It is a subclass of SpaceObject and contains information specific to rocket bodies, such as their record ID, NORAD ID, satellite name, country of origin, orbit type, and other relevant attributes.

      public RocketBody(int recordId, int noradId, String satelliteName, String country, String orbitType, String objectType, int launchYear, String launchSite, double longitude, double avgLongitude, String geoHash, int daysOld)
      Constructs a new RocketBody object with the specified attributes.
      Parameters:
      recordId - the unique identifier for the rocket body
      noradId - the NORAD catalog number assigned to the rocket body
      satelliteName - the name of the satellite associated with the rocket body
      country - the country of origin for the rocket body
      orbitType - the type of orbit the rocket body is in
      objectType - the type of object (in this case, "Rocket Body")
      launchYear - the year the rocket body was launched
      launchSite - the location from which the rocket body was launched
      longitude - the current longitude of the rocket body
      avgLongitude - the average longitude of the rocket body
      geoHash - the geohash representing the location of the rocket body
      daysOld - the number of days since the rocket body was launched
